5:
H-huh?! Did this thing just... teleport
us? Wh-where are we?!
22:
B-but why did you tell us about it?
Isn't it supposed to be a secret?
27:
...Mary. I might be able to find your
old home.
39:
The buildings, the ocean, the smell
of the tide... This is my old home.
43:
B-but I'm amazed you found it all on
your own, Reticia!
47:
You can thank House Felder. I
couldn't have done this on my own.
49:
...According to our records, your
parents should still be living here.
58:
Ah... Haha, it's weird...
I've missed my parents dearly for all
these years, but...
60:
...Well, it's just been so long. Maybe
they won't even recognize me...
68: ...I don't believe it. M-Mary! It's you!
70:
Mary, is that you?! I must be
dreaming!
76:
I see... So you've been working at a
confectionery with a couple that
took you in.
79:
Yeah, and they're both really nice
people. They raised me like I was
their own daughter...
82:
Everyone has been so kind to me
over there. I didn't want for anything.
85:
...That's... wonderful, Mary. I'm just so
happy to see that you're okay...
87:
...We knew we might never see you
again, but we never gave up hope.
88:
We've been keeping your bed ready
for the day you'd finally come home.
94:
...A-anyway, it's getting late, so
come stay with us! Bring your
friends too!
108:
...I loved this place. The sound of the
waves, my parents, everyone on the
Float...
110:
But one day, I suddenly ended up in
Palpebra... I couldn't hear the waves
anymore.
113:
I'm so selfish... My parents
remembered me right away and
looked so happy...
116:
In that moment, I should've said I
wanted to stay here from now on...
But I couldn't.
121:
...I think it's probably important to
think it over...
127:
It's okay to take your time to think
about heavy stuff like this.
129:
If you don't want to give up on
everything in Palpebra, why don't
you just tell them? We know you're
good at speaking your mind when
you want to.
134:
Yeah. Remember our little operation
the other day? I was ready to call it
off, but then you
140:
S-stop it, Reticia! Don't talk about
that with Will here!
149: You're important to me too, Mary.
156: Really, thank you! You're all the best...
162:
Leaving so soon, Mary? You can
stick around a little longer...
168:
I'm sorry... I can't come back to live
here with you.
171:
I want to keep working at the shop
with my other folks.
174:
There are lots of people in that city
that are really important to me, just
like you two.
178:
B-but I want to keep seeing you...
and I do still wish I could live with
you! So maybe I could come stay
over sometimes...
185:
You go live your life, Mary. There's
nothing selfish about chasing your
dreams.
192:
Come see us as often as you can,
okay? Every day, even! And if you
ever change your mind, you can
come live with us whenever you
want!
193:
Y-Yeah! We get lonely out here, you
know?! And there's so much we
want to talk about!
200:
Oh, there's one more thing I wanted
to tell you about!
203:
Once again, this is Will.
...And he's my boyfriend!
208:
Huh?! Since when?!
If I don't get an invitation to the
wedding, there'll be hell to pay!
